<br>
500 mana on orb<br>
150 Burnout<br>
750 Aegolism(or whatever HP)<br>
<br>
500+150+750 = 1400<br>
<br>
1400 &gt; 400<br>
<br>
Even on paper it's better, not to mention more convenient, than recasting a new pet.<br>
<br>
If you have to cast CH on the pet once a fight or more, it probably means you don't care that you aren't getting max xp, and that you're fighting in a place like Kael.<br>
<br>
Otherwise, your cleric will only be CHing the pet on occaision, and spending the rest of the time nuking, rodding, and healing rod damage.  Besides, clerics can rez, which means you can try crazy @#%$ and not worry about xp loss so long as you have a cr plan.<br>
<br>
I would say best partners are:<br>
<br>
Cleric<br>
Shaman<br>
Druid<br>
Mage<br>
Necro<br>
Ranger (Archer)<br>
Enchanter (Dire Charm)<br>
<br>
Paladin<br>
Wizard<br>
Monk<br>
Enchanter<br>
Ranger<br>
SK<br>
Bard<br>
Warrior<br>
Rogue<br>
<br>
No clue about beastlords, my guess is that they would make excellent partners, though. <p><center>
